passages.text: Reiterate Rating: UNDERPERFORM | PO: 6.54 CNY | Price: 8.72 CNY

Bank of Suzhou (BOSZ)'s 1H25 net profit grew \(6.2\%\) YoY, vs. \(6.8\%\) YoY in 1Q and missed BofAe by \(0.7\%\) . PPP growth accelerated to \(+7.4\%\) YoY in 1H25 from \(6.0\%\) in 1Q25. ROE fell by 1.1ppt YoY to \(12.4\%\) in 1H25. CET1 ratio up 44bp YoY or 7bp QoQ to \(9.87\%\) after CB conversion. We keep 2025- 27E earnings unchanged, lower cost of capital by 100bp on the enhanced capital strength, and lower PO by \(6\%\) to CNY6.54 (to reflect the dilution impact). Reiterate Underperform on softened earnings growth & dilution impact.

Net interest income (NII) rose \(2.3\%\) QoQ, with gross interest income/expense flat/fell by \(1.5\%\) QoQ respectively. NIM edged down by 1bp QoQ to \(1.33\%\) in 2Q25, or up 5bp HoH in 1H25. Loans grew \(0.2\%\) QoQ/ \(9.0\%\) HoH/ \(12\%\) YoY. Corporate loans, retail loans grew by \(13.4\% / - 2.5\%\) HoH, and made up \(108\% / - 8\%\) of the net new loans in 1H25. Discounted bills were compressed by \(38\%\) HoH. Loans issued to leasing & commercial service sector surged \(42\%\) HoH and became the largest contributor ( \(59\%\) ) of net new loans in 1H25. Mortgage /consumption loans up by \(0.6\% /8.3\%\) HoH, while personal business loans further declined \(12.1\%\) HoH. Assets/deposits grew \(3.8\% /0\%\) QoQ or \(14.5\% /11.6\%\) YoY. Net fee income slowed to \(9\%\) YoY from \(22\%\) in 1Q. Revenue rose \(1.9\%\) YoY in 1H, operating cost fell by \(7.6\%\) YoY driven by staff cost. CIR fell by 3.4ppt YoY to \(32.9\%\)

NPL size edged down \(0.3\%\) QoQ or rose \(9\%\) HoH, and NPL ratio remained stable QoQ/HoH at to \(0.83\%\) . Corporate loan NPL ratio stayed low and flat at \(0.51\%\) while retail loans NPL ratio rose by 14bp HoH to \(1.80\%\) in 1H25. NPL ratio of personal business loans/mortgage loans/consumption loans rose from \(3.18\% /0.41\% 1.23\%\) by 2024 to \(3.50\% /0.69\% /1.24\%\) by 1H25. Write- offs and gross NPL formation at 43bp/57bp in 1H25 were higher than 20bp/38bp in 1H24. Credit cost was at 37bp in 1H25, higher than 36bp in 1H24 but lower than 54bp in FY24. NPL and loan reserve coverage ratios fell QoQ/HoH/YoY to \(438\%\) and \(3.63\%\) .

Banks-Multinational/Universal

BOSZ was set up in 2004, formerly known as Dongwu Rural Commercial Bank, the 5th largest rural commercial bank across the country which developed from Suzhou municipal rural cooperative union in Suzhou city. Listed on 2 August, 2019, BOSZ is the only legal city commercial bank in Suzhou, the first to convert from rural to city commercial bank and the 9th listed bank in Jiangsu province. It is the 12th largest A- share listed city commercial bank in China by assets, as of 1Q23

BOSZ had several red flags in our asset quality review: 1) its credit costs continued to decline against higher gross NPL formation. As a result, NPL and reserve coverage decreased QoQ/HoH/YoY. 2) its overdue and SML formations were relatively high. 3) Property developer loans surged. 4) Retail loans showed significant increase in NPLs, its retail loan/personal business NPL formations were one of the highest among our covered banks. We rate BOSZ at Underperform.

Our CNY6.54 PO (from CNY6.94) is based on 0.58x 2025- 26E P/B (from 0.54x) assuming medium- term ROE of \(11.2\%\) (from \(11.3\%\) ), medium- term sustainable growth of \(4.0\%\) and cost of equity of \(16.5\%\) (from \(17.5\%\) ) on enhanced capital. At our PO, the stock would be trading at 5.6x 2025- 26E P/E or 3.6x 2025- 26E P/PPOP.

Downside risks to our PO are higher- than- expected credit- cost, a marked deterioration in asset quality, and worse- than- expected margin decline, potentially due to unfavorable interest rate changes.
Upside risks are the potentially better- than- expected margin performance and lower- than- expected NPL formation.
